3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates funding rates hourly using a premium-based mechanism that compares perpetual prices to spot references. The Starknet settlement layer enables precise execution without gas costs for position adjustments. Cross-margin capabilities allow efficient capital deployment across multiple positions. Funding payments occur automatically through the protocol's smart contract infrastructure, with rates typically ranging from -0.5% to +0.5% in normal market conditions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PYTH","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PYTH's infrastructure focus creates distinct funding rate patterns compared to traditional DeFi tokens, often showing premium during oracle network adoption phases. The token's mid-tier volume on RabbitX provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage while maintaining rate volatility that creates profit opportunities. Oracle token correlations with broader market infrastructure needs generate predictable funding rate cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PYTH funding rates on RabbitX exhibit strong correlation with oracle network usage spikes and DeFi protocol integrations. During major oracle updates or new chain deployments, funding rates frequently shift positive as demand for long exposure increases. The hourly reset mechanism captures these movements more granularly than 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges. Rate volatility typically peaks during US trading hours when institutional oracle demand is highest. Weekend periods often see negative funding as retail long interest wanes."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's zero gas fee structure enables profitable arbitrage on funding rate differentials as low as 0.01% against other PYTH perpetual venues. The cross-margin system allows simultaneous long/short positions to capture rate spreads without additional collateral requirements. Starknet's fast finality supports rapid position adjustments when funding rate predictions shift. Best opportunities typically emerge during Asian trading hours when RabbitX rates diverge from Binance and OKX due to lower DEX arbitrage activity. The protocol's early-stage nature creates temporary inefficiencies that sophisticated traders can exploit."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's limited user base creates higher slippage risk during volatile periods, potentially offsetting funding rate gains through adverse execution. The protocol's early-stage development introduces smart contract risks and potential downtime during network congestion. PYTH's correlation with broader oracle sector movements can create unexpected directional exposure beyond funding rate strategies. Cross-margin positions amplify liquidation risks if underlying PYTH price moves against combined exposure. Limited insurance fund coverage compared to established CEXs increases counterparty risk during extreme market events."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does RabbitX's 1-hour funding rate benefit PYTH arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The hourly funding rate captures PYTH's intraday volatility patterns more precisely than 8-hour cycles, allowing arbitrageurs to exploit oracle network usage spikes and institutional trading flows. This granular settlement reduces the risk of rate reversals between payment periods."},{"question":"What makes PYTH funding rates unique on Starknet-based exchanges?","answer":"Starknet's zero gas fees eliminate the execution costs that typically eat into funding rate profits on Ethereum mainnet. The infrastructure also enables more sophisticated cross-margin strategies where PYTH positions can be hedged against other oracle tokens efficiently."},{"question":"How reliable is RabbitX for large funding rate arbitrage positions?","answer":"RabbitX's limited liquidity requires position sizing below $50k for optimal execution. The protocol's off-chain matching provides good fills for medium-sized trades, but large arbitrage positions may face slippage that reduces funding rate advantages."},{"question":"What oracle network events typically drive PYTH funding rate spikes?","answer":"Major blockchain integrations, DeFi protocol migrations to Pyth price feeds, and network governance updates typically drive positive funding rates as institutions increase long exposure. These events create predictable patterns that experienced arbitrageurs monitor closely."}]}]
